The task is to create a private EKS cluster using the default VPC, ensure high availability, and follow internal security standards.
Step 1: Create IAM Role for EKS Cluster
Navigate to IAM → Roles → Create role.
Trusted entity: AWS service → EKS
Use case: EKS Cluster
Attach Policies:
AmazonEKSClusterPolicy
AmazonEKSServicePolicy
Role Name: eksClusterRole
Click Create role.
This role allows EKS to manage resources on your behalf.
Step 2: Create the EKS Cluster (Console Method)
Navigate to EKS → Clusters → Create cluster → Custom configuration.
Cluster Name: nautilus-eks
Kubernetes Version: Select the latest stable version.
Cluster Endpoint Access: Select Private only (disable public endpoint).
VPC Configuration:
VPC: Default VPC
Subnets: Select private subnets in Availability Zones a, b, c
Security Groups: Default or create a custom security group allowing control plane access from your internal network.
IAM Role: eksClusterRole
EKS Auto Mode: Ensure disabled (manual node group management)
Click Create Cluster.
